The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Sept. 1 (PTI): The Delhi government today launched two mobile courts for the prosecution of beggars in a bid to free the city of 60,000 beggars ahead of the Commonwealth Games.           
	Each mobile court will have a retired judge, a policeman and an official from the department of social welfare.                   
	 Thiruvananthapuram (PTI): A six-year-old girl, inmate of a home for children near Thiruvananthapuram, was allegedly hit on her chest and arms with a hot iron bar by an employee for wetting her bed at night. The girls mother learnt of the incident when she came to take the girl home for the Onam vacation.                   
	 Mandi (PTI): At least 24 people were killed and nine injured when a private bus in which they were travelling fell into a gorge in Mandi district of Himachal Pradesh on Tuesday evening. The bodies of all 24 passengers have been taken out of the bus, Mandi deputy commissioner Onkar Sharma said. The injured have been admitted to hospital, he added.                   
	 Bijapur (PTI): An 18-month-old girl fell into an abandoned borewell in a field on Monday near Bijapur in Karnataka. Efforts are on to rescue her. Oxygen is being supplied to Eagavva, the child, through a tube, officials said. Assistance from army personnel has been sought, they added.                                                                                                                           
